21
Subtitle
22
23 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING PROHIBITED
24 CONTRACTS BY STATE AGENCIES; AND TO
25 PROHIBIT THE USE OF PUBLIC FUNDS BY
26 STATE AGENCIES TO PURCHASE PROMOTIONAL
27 ITEMS MADE IN CHINA.
28
29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
30
31 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 25-1-1202, concerning the definitions for
32 the laws on prohibited contracts by state agencies, is amended to add
33 additional subdivisions to read as follows:
34 (5) "Promotional items" means one (1) or more items purchased by
35 a state agency with public funds to promote or advertise the agency,
36 including without limitation a:
*LGL120*
03-20-2025 15:43:04 LGL120

As Engrossed: H3/17/25 S3/20/25 HB1604
1 (A) Bumper sticker;
2 (B) Clothing item;
3 (C) Key chain;
4 (D) Mug;
5 (E) Pen; or
6 (F) Pin;
7 (6) "Public funds" means the same as defined in ยง 19-11-203;
8
9 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 25, Chapter 1, Subchapter 12, is
10 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
11 25-1-1204. Promotional items made in China prohibited.
12 A state agency shall not spend public funds to purchase promotional
13 items made in the People's Republic of China.
14
15 SECTION 3. DO NOT CODIFY. The name of Arkansas Code Title 25, Chapter
16 1, Subchapter 12 is changed from "Prohibited Contracts by State Agencies" to
17 "Prohibited Actions by State Agencies." The Arkansas Code Revision Commission
18 shall make all changes in the Arkansas Code necessary to implement this
19 section.
20
21 SECTION 4. DO NOT CODIFY. Applicability.
22 Sections 1 and 2 of this act apply only to contracts executed on or
23 after the effective date of this act.
